      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "no portion, nor right, nor memorial",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] These words closely resemble the declaration in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 4:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and imply some sort of claim on the part of these adversaries to a share in the fortunes of Jerusalem. If so, the adversaries must be regarded as mainly consisting of the Samaritan community. Nehemiah renouncing connexion with the Samaritans, affirms that they have no share in the present community, no ground for claiming it in the future, no memorial or justification of such claim in the past.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "no portion",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 20:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
