  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 20.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Then answered I.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " It is remarkable that Nehemiah takes no notice of the serious charge brought against him, does not say that he had the king's permission, but rather leaves the \"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "adversaries\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " to suppose that he had not. Perhaps he thought that to reveal the truth would drive them to some desperate attempt, and therefore suppressed it",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": ". The God of heaven, he will prosper us",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Instead of a human, Nehemiah claims a Divine sanction for his proceedings. He and his brethren will build as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "servants of the God of heaven.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Compare the answer made to Tatnai in Zerubbabel's time - \"We are ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "the servants of the God of heaven",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and earth, and build the house that was builded these many years ago\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 5:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "). Ye have no portion, nor right, nor memorial, in Jerusalem.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " As the claim of the Samaritans to interfere in the affairs of the Jews had been disallowed when they came with an offer of aid (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 4:2, 3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), so now, when their interference is hostile in character, it is still more fiercely and indignantly rejected. They are told that they have no part in Jerusalem, no right, not even so much as a place in the recollections of the inhabitants. Their interference is officious, impertinent - what have they to do with Nehemiah, or the Israelites, or Jerusalem? Let them be content to manage the affairs of their own idolatrous community, and not trouble the worshippers of the true God. Nehemiah avoids opposition by concealment as long as he can; but when opposition nevertheless appears, he meets it with defiance. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Nehemiah 2:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
